-- Lebanon Jails Seven People for Collaborating With Israel, Daily Star Says
-- Massoud A. Derhally
-- 2010-06-18T06:19:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-18/lebanon-jails-seven-people-for-collaborating-with-israel-daily-star-says.html

          
          
             A Lebanese military tribunal
sentenced seven people yesterday to 15 years of hard labor for
collaborating with Israel, entering Israeli territories and
acquiring Israeli nationality, the  Daily Star  reported.  
 Judge Nizar Khalil sentenced Lebanese citizens Beshara
Ibrahim Saeed, Milad Hanna Hashem, Afif Jirji Atieh, Moussa Dib
Daoud, Hanna Salim Hashem, Daoud Boutros al-Nadaf and Jirjis
Naji al-Nadaf to 15 years and fined them each 1 million pounds
($666), the  newspaper  reported.  
 Israel and Lebanon are technically at war and have no
diplomatic relations.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
 Massoud A. Derhally  in Beirut, Lebanon at   mderhally@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        